  <refnamediv>
    <refname>imadd</refname>
    <refpurpose>Add the contents of 2 matrices or images and store it in another</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   outputMat = imadd(input1, input2)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>input1 :</term>
      <listitem><para> First input matrix or an image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>input2 :</term>
      <listitem><para> Second input matrix or image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
Z = imadd(X,Y) adds each element in array X with the corresponding element in array Y and returns the sum in the corresponding element of the output array Z. X and Y are real, nonsparse numeric arrays with the same size and class, or Y is a scalar double. Z has the same size and class as X, unless X is logical, in which case Z is double.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
a = [1 5 6;4 2 3];
b = [8 10 15;5 1 9];
c = imadd(a,b);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
a = imread("lena.jpeg");
b = imread("lena1.jpeg");
c = imadd(a,b);
imshow(c)

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

